      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "World Central Kitchen's financial model is built for speed and scale. With <cite id=\"3\">$241,549,612 in revenue</cite>, the organization has the capacity to mobilize millions of dollars in aid almost instantly. Their <cite id=\"3\">92.5% program expense ratio</cite> is a standout metric in the humanitarian sector, where many organizations struggle to keep administrative costs below 15%. Furthermore, the charity's <cite id=\"1\">100% independent board</cite> provides strong oversight, ensuring that these vast resources are managed with accountability. This combination of high liquidity and low overhead allows WCK to act as a 'first-responder' that can sustain long-term feeding operations in places like <cite id=\"4\">Ukraine and Gaza</cite>."
